Id":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#trading","cachedResultName":"#trading"},"text":"=✅ Monitor stock levels with HTTP / REST API and Outlook without manual w — run completed at {{ $now.toFormat('HH:mm') }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[5238,400],"id":"65cb97fd-a7c2-44cf-a207-20687dd5a7d9","name":"Send Summary to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"0ebceddf-43ed-41cd-9bf0-ff9025721375","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"38fb2b4f-79e8-4c7a-ab0e-ca70bfc54bc9","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"32711daa-2796-44c5-8890-5c7528345a62","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[4590,1420],"id":"187f5d7e-139b-4baf-b85b-42ccfe27f2fe","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#trading","cachedResultName":"#trading"},"text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[4914,1420],"id":"705980fa-6860-469e-9c58-1b0ff1c6d6b6","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Every Few Minutes\n\nStarts the workflow on a timer — every 5 min. No input data; downstream nodes fetch what they need.\n\nNext: Probe Endpoint A","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"fbd64dee-75b6-8daf-dd01-debd60b55ffd","name":"Note: Every Few Minutes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint A\n\nGET https://service-a.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,250],"id":"6622e033-c5b3-47f6-63b8-577fa1d2d214","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint A"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint B\n\nGET https://service-b.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,760],"id":"584c8911-e5aa-cd9f-124b-72018bfb4ad4","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint B"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Combine Probe Results\n\nRejoins 2 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: All Healthy?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,520],"id":"c2fd9192-d127-f93f-c751-aaccd0389161","name":"Note: Combine Probe Results"},{"parameters":{"content":"### All Healthy?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ ($json.statusCode || 200) < 400 }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Uptime Metric · ②→ Already Alerted? (State Check)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1938,520],"id":"1c132117-b91b-c88e-4b23-6bdc65e90368","name":"Note: All Healthy?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Uptime Metric\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Save Execution Metadata · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,280],"id":"7c1c5c46-b451-ae2b-1928-19f5a0bcdaa9","name":"Note: Record Uptime Metric"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Already Alerted? (State Check)\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Page On-Call via Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,880],"id":"182f99fb-c6d9-a740-6380-abc5ebc00628","name":"Note: Already Alerted? (State Check)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Page On-Call via Slack\n\nmicrosoftOutlook — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3234,880],"id":"df98fc73-26b1-d249-33fc-032ede418001","name":"Note: Page On-Call via Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Sort Assets Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"288a913a-ab37-3aca-60e2-35caab8ab5bc","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Assets Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Tag Pipeline Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"cd78c630-e032-2b7b-f2f6-7f3f4e5d52d1","name":"Note: Sort Assets Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\nShapes the item: writes `pipeline`, `version`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Send Summary to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"78e67640-3ea8-f299-8a35-200e9afb7f00","name":"Note: Tag Pipeline Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"3f85bb26-fb0b-1ba6-5990-f7489f650507","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,1540],"id":"fbf22270-d73c-b865-1e50-014e4b56bdb8","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,1540],"id":"91a9387b-afb5-2e0d-e3cc-4d9a44f39624","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Monitor stock levels with HTTP / REST API and Outlook without manual work\n\n**Pattern:** Threshold Monitoring · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nMonitor stock levels with HTTP / REST API and Outlook without manual work. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual price alerts is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nEvery Few Minutes → Probe Endpoint A → Combine Probe Results → All Healthy? → Record Uptime Metric → Save Execution Metadata → Sort Assets Newest First → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to threshold monitoring without manual effort\n- Anyone automating price alerts in finance\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"16e92427-019a-6c4c-aff0-17f1ac6f42e6","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-290],"id":"62b5158a-020d-269b-35b8-190c4e8396f3","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-290],"id":"1794b6ac-ee28-47ad-a37b-88cfe3adf1e6","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your price alerts process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-290],"id":"16a532b7-3c04-ac94-32c2-29e6888c8d17","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Every Few Minutes":{"main":[[{"node":"Probe Endpoint A","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Probe Endpoint B","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Probe Endpoint A":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Probe Endpoint B":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":1}]]},"Combine Probe Results":{"main":[[{"node":"All Healthy?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"All Healthy?":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Uptime Metric","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Already Alerted? (State Check)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Already Alerted? (State Check)":{"main":[[{"node":"Page On-Call via Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Uptime Metric":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Assets Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Assets Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Tag Pipeline Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Tag Pipeline Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Page On-Call via Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"7550f6cc-9929-44ef-8d09-496df37b82c1","id":"FDX08951"}